J&T Global Express Ltd (1519. HK) Price Target
From To HK\\$9.50 HK\\$9.10
Unchanged Impact to our thesis
Modest shortfall Financial results versus consensus
Modest revision lower Direction of next 12-month consensus EPS
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research
1H25 earnings miss on China amid intensified competition but growth outlook in SEA and New Markets seems intact. Stay EW on full valuation.

1H25 results - robust SEA growth in- line, but China miss: J&T reported 1H25 adj. NP of US\\$156mn, 33% lower vs. MSe of US\\$234mn. SEA was in line with 74% growth in adj. EBIT. China reported 78% YoY adj. EBIT drop amid intensified competition. New Markets saw a slight beat with adj. EBITDA turning around earlier than expected thanks to new EC customers entering the market and cooperation with MELI.

Takeaways from result call: 1) J&T achieved 5.4ppt YoY market share in SEA in 1H25 with solid efficiency advantages over 3PL peers thanks to robust volume growth; 2) J&T expects volume growth in New Markets to accelerate with fast market share gain in the next 2- 3 years thanks to investments from EC customers. 3) J&T expects NP in China to improve HoH but thinks volume growth may slow down amid industry "anti- involution".

Earnings forecasts and PT adjustments. We cut adjusted NP by 17%, 8% and 16% for 2025- 27, respectively. We factor in better outlook in New Markets, and lower the profit recovery outlook in China given its 1H25 miss. Our weighted price target drops 4% to HK\\$9.1, after rolling forward the valuation date to end- 2026.

Stay EW. We think the strong growth outlook in SEA is intact and New Markets should also contribute profit from 2H25. However, China remains a drag given its sustained negative FCF. We think the market has priced in earnings upside from SEA and New Markets. J&T is trading at 32x 2025 P/E and 2% 2025e FCF yield, which looks full.

Why not Ow: 1) China business will likely remain a drag in terms of free cash flow, potentially delaying J&T's shareholder returns; 2) competition with e- commerce self- built logistics remains a potential challenge in SEA and New Markets. 3) market expectation looks full after its recent rally.
MORGAN STANLEY ASIA LIMITED+
Qianlei Fan, CFA Equity Analyst
Benny Song Equity Analyst
J&T Global Express Ltd (1519. HK, 1519 HK)
Hong Kong/China Transportation & Infrastructure | Hong Kong

- Management expects market growth to stay robust in the next five years, and continues to target market share gains in the region.- Unit EBIT to stay relatively stable with sustained cost reduction.- Tiktok remains its largest customer in SEA.- Thailand market's loss making has narrowed, and achieved profitability in several months this year.

- Tiktok and Temu entered the LatAm market in 1H25. Management sees the potential of more e-commerce players entering this market.- Chinese e-commerce players are penetrating into local e-commerce market (in contrast to cross-border e-commerce) in LatAm.- J&T has also started collaboration with MELI, to cover areas where MELI has relatively weaker presence.- J&T has only a small percentage ( \(\sim 10\%\) ) of total capex spent in New Markets, and expects to start to invest more heavily when its market share is over \(10\%\) .- Management thinks unit EBIT in LatAm market should be higher versus SEA given its higher per capita GDP.

- China market remains important to J&T given its leading efficiencies and technology in express delivery business.- Management thinks 2H25 China adjusted EBIT could be better vs. 1H25.- J&T currently has \(\sim 900\) unmanned electronic vehicles in its China network

We cut our respective adjusted net income (including minority interest) estimates for 2025/2026/2027e by \(17\% /8\% /16\%\) , to US \(4.12mn / US\) \(\) 590mn/\(US\) 734mn. Our adjusted EBITDA forecasts are cut by - 9.3\% / - 9.9\% / - 11.3\% for the respective years.

- SEA: We raise our adjusted EBITDA estimates by 2\%/1\%/1\% for 2025e/2026e/2027e.- China: We lower our adjusted EBITDA estimates by 24\%/28\%/29\% for 2025/2026/2027e, considering intensified market competition in China.- New Markets: Our adjusted EBITDA estimates are raised by 400\%/84\%/10\% for 2025/2026/2027e (low base), on J&T's healthy expansion in new markets.
Source: Morgan Stanley Research (E) estimates

2025e, 2026e and 2027e revenue growth \(21\%\) , \(20\%\) and \(17\%\) ; adjusted EBIT margin \(+7\%\) , \(+8\%\) and \(+8\%\) , respectively. We assume stronger volume growth in 2025- 27 than in our base case, led by outperformance in SE Asia operations as well as strong demand from China and new markets.

2025e, 2026e and 2027e revenue growth \(17\%\) , \(16\%\) , and \(13\%\) , respectively, and adjusted EBIT margin \(+4\%\) , \(+5\%\) and \(+6\%\) . We expect industry volume CAGRs in SE Asia, China, and new markets at \(19\%\) , \(12\%\) , and \(20\%\) , respectively, over 2025- 27e. J&T maintains its market share gain momentum, achieving 17.6ppt, 0.0ppt, and 2.5ppt market share in SE Asia, China, and new markets, respectively, over 2025e, 2026e and 2027e. We expect GP margin in SE Asia to improve from \(18.7\%\) in 2025 to \(19.9\%\) in 2027 while China drops from \(4.9\%\) in 2025 to \(4.6\%\) in 2027.

2025e, 2026e and 2027e revenue growth \(14\%\) , \(13\%\) and \(10\%\) ; adjusted EBIT margin \(+2\%\) , \(+3\%\) and \(+3\%\) , respectively. We assume slower market volume growth in 2025- 27 than in our base case; ASP remains under pressure amid competition, leading to slower- than- expected revenue growth, and market share gains and profit improvement are constrained by intensifying competition.
Strong growth momentum in SEA, but China growth under pressure; EW
WACC of \(13.3\%\) (risk- free rate of \(4.0\%\) and adjusted beta of 1.15) Terminal growth rate of \(3.5\%\)

We see volume growth potential in Southeast Asia (SEA) and new markets (Saudi Arabia, UAE, Mexico, Brazil, Egypt), and expect J&T to further expand its market share in SEA. China could remain a drag by generating negative free cash flow in future. Competition from IP logistics in SEA and New Markets remain a concern to us. Our price target implies \(25x\) 2025e P/E, more expensive vs. Chinese peers due to faster growth overseas.
